In microbiology and cellular biology, getting an
accurate estimate of the number of viable cells
in solution is important. A common approach
involves spreading a known volume of a cell
suspension on agar plates to enumerate the
number of colonies after growth. The counting
is often performed manually. This task is time
consuming and quite subjective. During the last decade, a few
authors have targeted this question and developed solutions, but
OpenCFU is very close to Humans.
